examples.sentence: Los protocolos de seguridad son importantes.

etymology.value: From Spanish protocolo, from Latin protocollum, from Ancient Greek πρωτόκολλον (prōtókollon, “first sheet of papyrus glued to a manuscript; table of contents; protocol”), from πρῶτος (prôtos, “first”) + κόλλα (kólla, “glue”).

usage_notes.explanation: 'Protocolos' is the plural form of the Spanish word 'protocolo', which translates to 'protocol' in English. It refers to a set of rules or procedures.
